title: Whitney Houston
author: PatrickBateman_
pages:
#- Did you know that Whitney Houston's debut LP, called simply Whitney Houston, had four number one singles on it?
#- It's hard to choose a favorite among so many great tracks, but "The Greatest Love of All" is one of the best, most powerful songs ever written about self-preservation, dignity.
#- Its universal message crosses all boundaries and instills one with the hope that it's not too late to better ourselves.
#- Since it's impossible in this world we live in to empathize with others, we can always empathize with ourselves.
#- It's an important message, crucial really. And it's beautifully stated on the album.
#- 